2
00:00:13,830 --> 00:00:19,480
How do you connect up what they&#39;re saying, the words that are coming into your auditory

3
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:24,589
system with what they mean, what they refer to?

4
00:00:24,589 --> 00:00:28,510
One hypothesis is that you do it through association.

5
00:00:28,510 --> 00:00:33,540
Babies are looking at something like a bottle, and they hear somebody say, &quot;Do you like your

6
00:00:33,540 --> 00:00:34,540
bottle?

7
00:00:34,540 --> 00:00:36,270
Look at your yellow bottle.&quot;

8
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:41,371
With that nice infant-directed speech, it’s very clear that bottle is the word, the thing

9
00:00:41,371 --> 00:00:43,160
that&#39;s being highlighted.

10
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:47,649
They&#39;re looking at the bottle, so they link up what they hear, “bottle”, with what

11
00:00:47,649 --> 00:00:50,719
they see and thereby learn the word.

12
00:00:50,719 --> 00:00:55,760
That&#39;s one solution and in fact, that was the solution that was proposed some centuries

13
00:00:55,760 --> 00:01:00,260
